## **DIRECTOR'S SUMMARY – Q4 PROCUREMENT CYCLE**

### **Cycle Complete: $483,500 Committed + Strategic Escalation**

This quarter's procurement cycle has successfully addressed urgent inventory 
shortages on two critical components while evaluating a significant multi-year 
supplier proposal. 

**Two components were sourced and committed:**
1. **controller_board_v3** (URGENT: 2.1 weeks cover) — **10,000 units sourced 
from Helix Microsystems at $398,000**. Helix was selected for proven operational
excellence (99.4% on-time, 0.2% defect rate), supply security (6-week lead time 
with 3-week production buffer), and sourcing flexibility. Inventory restored to 
safe levels within 6 weeks.

2. **harness_assembly_a** (HIGH PRIORITY: 3.0 weeks cover, elevated supply risk,
Arc capacity-constrained) — **5,000 units sourced from Arc Wirecraft at 
$85,500** via aggressive forward-buy. Volume-tier pricing locked in 
($17.10/unit); post-purchase inventory rises to 7,800+ units (8–9 weeks cover), 
mitigating single-source risk during volatile supply period. Secondary-source 
qualification initiated in parallel.

**One strategic proposal escalated to CFO/Legal:**
**Meridian Electronics** has proposed a 36-month exclusive for 
controller_board_v3 at $30/unit with $2.0M upfront capital commitment. Financial
modeling reveals this would cost **$3.01M more than baseline** (Helix spot buy) 
and represents **extreme counterparty risk** (unverified supplier, no QBR 
history). Negotiation template analysis recommends conditional acceptance only 
if Meridian qualifies and accepts a **24-month counter-offer ($1.0M upfront, 50%
volume flexibility)**, netting modest savings ($64k) while preserving 
supply-chain independence. **Due diligence checklist** (credit check, 
references, bankruptcy verification, quality audit) has been prepared for 
CFO/Legal; decision gate at week 2 will determine whether to approve 
counter-offer, reject, or trigger dual-source strategy.

**Governance:** Both Helix and Arc commitments are HITL-approved and 
execution-ready (PO issuance pending director sign-off). Meridian decision is 
escalated and conditional on supplier verification. Lithium cells and thermal 
paste remain in good standing; no action required. Open items include Meridian 
due diligence (2-week timeline), secondary harness_assembly_a qualification (4 
weeks), and Arc long-term contract exploration.

**Total at-risk spend: $483,500 committed + $1.5M–$2.0M pending (Meridian 
escalation, CFO/Legal approval-gated).**

---

**The Q4 cycle is complete. Recommendation document is board-ready for 
